    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I like @Carreau's suggestion which now brings a stylistic question.\r\n\r\nI'm seeing other places in the docs where `.. only::` is used.\r\n\r\nWould you prefer an _additional_ note with an `.. only:: ipydev` directive,\r\n```\r\n.. only:: ipydev\r\n\r\nFor beta (pre-release) installations, use:\r\n  .. code::\r\n\r\n     pip install ipython --upgrade --pre\r\n```\r\nor an alternating pair of:\r\n```\r\n.. only:: ipydev\r\n\r\n  .. code::\r\n\r\n     pip install ipython --upgrade --pre\r\n\r\n.. only:: not ipydev\r\n\r\n  .. code::\r\n\r\n     pip install ipython --upgrade\r\n```"
  },
